Charles Rock https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_Rock 0 Charles Rock (30 May 1866 – 12 July 1919) was a British actor. He was born Arthur Charles Rock de Fabeck. Rock also wrote at least one play titled "The Ghost of Jerry Bundler", adapted from W. W. Jacobs' story Jerry Bundler. It was cast at the Haymarket Theatre Sept. 9, 1902, with Rock starring as the character George (waiter). Charles_Rock ( 30_May_1866 – 12_July_1919 ) was a_British_actor .
